# AWS Auto Scaling Lab – EC2 → ALB → Target Group → Launch Template → Auto Scaling

## Lab Objective

EC2 Instance → Target Group → Application Load Balancer → Launch Template → Auto Scaling Group → CPU Utilization Scaling

The web server installation will be automated using **User Data Script**.
---
# Architecture

User → Application Load Balancer → Target Group → Auto Scaling Group → EC2 Instances

---
# Prerequisites

Before starting the lab ensure you have:

* AWS Account
* EC2 Key Pair
* Basic knowledge of AWS EC2
* Security Group allowing SSH and HTTP

---
# Task 1 – Create EC2 Instance

Login to AWS Console.

Navigate to:

EC2 → Instances → Launch Instance

Configuration:

Name
web-server

AMI
Amazon Linux 2

Instance Type
t2.micro

Key Pair
Select existing key pair

Security Group Rules

SSH – Port 22 – My IP
HTTP – Port 80 – Anywhere

---
# Task 2 – Install Web Server using User Data

In **Advanced Details → User Data**, add the following script.

```bash
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "<h1>Welcome to AWS Auto Scaling Lab</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
```

Launch the instance.
After instance is running, verify the website using:

```
http://<EC2-Public-IP>
```

