# Task 10 – Test Auto Scaling using CPU Load

Connect to the running EC2 instance using SSH.

Example

```
ssh ec2-user@<instance-ip>
```

Generate CPU load.

```bash
yes > /dev/null &
```

Check CPU usage.

```bash
top
```

When CPU usage exceeds **50%**, Auto Scaling will automatically launch a new EC2 instance.

Verify in:

EC2 → Auto Scaling Groups → Activity

---

# Stop CPU Load

```bash
killall yes
```

---

# Verify Scaling

Check:

EC2 → Instances

You should see a **new instance launched automatically**.

---

# Cleanup (Important)

To avoid AWS charges delete the following resources.

1. Auto Scaling Group
2. Load Balancer
3. Target Group
4. EC2 Instances
5. Launch Template

